<Author>PeepOregon
<Content>Very disappointed I had gone on this web site to check out this property as I learned straight away that it was not a Paradore any more.Their web page did not work and my email to them bounced back. I then had to call them to book. Decided to go anyway after reading reviews.Very disappointed. First, it is now owned by the city of Jayuya and is no longer private. We asked for room 4 as Foders or Frommers suggested that room 4 and 5 were the best (last years book) We knew it would be rustic but little things were not right like my husband had to crawl under the bed to plug in the lamp (he isn't getting any younger!) There were 3 light bulbs out in the ceiling and one on the deck. The ceiling fan did not work. Ironically, the beds were OK (reading reviews said otherwise) Then in the morning, there was water all over the floor in the bathroom (toilet or? who knows) There had been a rain storm the night before. Also the bathroom was the smallest we had ever ever been in. Very basic all together but sort of expected that.The food was terrible......we both ordered a meat with beans and rice and got dried meat (chicken and pork) Very basic menu. The breakfast was no better.I have to say the staff was very pleasant especially the man at the front desk. The pool was too cold. The bar was closed as apparently they were having problems with their liquor licence.It is such a shame as the surrounding area was lovely and the main dining area and seating areas were charming. It just needs better management. 
