<Content>Off the Beaten Track Simply driving through the mountains to get to Hacienda Grapinas is an adventure and is well worth it. The mountains in PR offer another world. The Parador is an old coffee plantation. The setting was lovely and the porches had extended views and were very comfortable. the place was very tastefully decorated. I had one complaint about the rooms. I had read that you did not need air conditioning because there were fans and you could keep the windows open and get the cool mountain air. In fact the fans did not work and you were compelled to use the air conditioning. The restaurant is very good. There are excellant short hikes along the roads outside past hills where coffee is grown. Within a short distance there is true excellant mountain hiking at Toro Negro State Forest, which offers very much the same experieince one would get at El Yunque. 
