<Content>Worth the time and effort Hacienda Gripinas was worth the travel time and effort. I promised to show my wife traditional mainland Puerto Rico. After staying in Old San Juan for 3 days, we were ready for a more relaxed atmosphere. The drive to Jayuja from San Juan takes about 2 hours. Our reception at the Hacienda was warm and friendly. Our room,# 5, was modestly furnished, clean and very acceptable. It had a private balcony which overlooked the main pool area.Breakfast and Dinner were part of our package. These meals were served in a clean and spacious dining room.The food was adequate, delicious and well presented.My wife and I don,t need a lot of entertainment. We took walks, read, and explored the Toro Negro. Without a doubt, We would return to Hacienda Gripinas...It was a highlight of our vacation. 
