<Content>Honeymoon Paradise If you want to get away from all the loud and fast pace hotels. I definitely recommend Hacienda Gipinas. It was a little difficult in getting there but the travel was well worth it. It you love the Mountains and living with Nature you will Love Hacienda Gripinas. It was my first time in seven years that I got a chance to escape with my wife and we loved the atmosphere. As soon as you get there mountains will surround you and you actually notice the rich smell of nature in the air. The Hacienda has a cozy restaurant and the food is very good. Nearby you will have some tours that you can take and see some Indian carvings on rocks that are over 500 years old. You can visit coffee plantations and buy Puerto Rico grown coffee. Nearby you can go to the highest point in Puerto Rico, which has a Spectacular view.The people are very hospitable and they are always there to tend to your needs. The rates are great and they have Honeymoon packages as well. I recommend this Hacienda to everyone. Have fun in Puerto Rico. 
